This paper discusses the intersection of machine learning and social sciences, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper focuses on the potential harm caused by machine learning when applied without care, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also emphasizes the importance of social theory in addressing these issues, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of cs.CY (Computers and Society) or cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper walks through every step of the machine learning pipeline, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of cs.CS (Computer Science and Game Theory).
